content:
Add Social Accounts to Social Customer Service

Social Customer Service is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Service Setup is available in Lightning Experience.

To administer Social Customer Service:

Manage Users

AND

Customize Application

To create case feed items: Feed Tracking for All Related Objects on the Case object
To make attachment download links public: Create Public Links

If you aren’t using the start pack, you can synchronize up to 2,000 managed social accounts from Social Studio. Agents can respond from all synced accounts from the social publisher on the case feed.

From Setup, enter Social Media in the Quick Find box, then select Social Customer Service.
On the Social Accounts tab, click Add Account and select a social network.
Click the refresh icon next to Add Account.
Select case creation options.
If you are using the Starter Pack, check the Case Creation box...
If you have a portfolio of managed social accounts, set the Default Responses From for each Twitter, Instagram, and Sina Weibo account.

WARNING If you delete a Social Account, it’s deleted everywhere, including Social Studio, and you can’t retrieve the deleted account.
title: Setting Up and Configuring Social Customer Service in Salesforce
